data.name: Server Error
data.description: The model describes the error returned if anythings goes wrong when the server logic is being executed.

data.name: copyright
data.description: Copyright notice for content of the seed. It matches the "copyright" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: description
data.description: The detailed description of the seed. It matches the "description" element of the RSS channel.  You can leave it blank, and it will be automatically retrieved from the corresponding feed. Otherwise, it will be overwritten.

data.name: docs
data.description: The URL that points to the documentation about RSS. According to RSS board, it will never change, so we default it to http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification. You are more than welcome to specify your own URL to the documentation about your seed. It matches the "docs" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: image_url
data.description: The URL to the image associated with the seed.

data.name: language
data.description: The language that the seed is written in. It matches the "language" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: last_build_date
data.description: The date when the content of the seed was changed. It matches the "last_build_date" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: link
data.description: The URL of the source. It matches the "link" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: managing_editor
data.description: Contact information of the publisher or other content responsible party. It matches the "managing_editor" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: pub_date
data.description: The date when the content of the seed was officially published. It matches the "pub_date" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: rating
data.description: The PICS rating for the seed. It matches the "rating" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: skip_days
data.description: Specific days of the week when the seed should not be read. Can contain up to sever days. It matches "skip_days" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: skip_hours
data.description: Specific hours of the day when the seed should not be read. Can contain up to 24 hours, each is between 0 and 23. It matches "skip_hours" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: title
data.description: The name of the seed. It matches the "title" element of the RSS channel.  You can leave it blank, and it will be automatically retrieved from the corresponding feed. Otherwise, it will be overwritten.

data.name: ttl
data.description: Time-to-live. Time that defines how often the seed should be updated. It matches the "ttl" element of the RSS channel.

data.name: web_master
data.description: Contact information for the technical support. It matches the "web_master" element of the RSS channel.
The method subscribes you to the seed. If the seed does not exist, it creates a new seed based on the provided link and retrieves feed entries. Note: all non-URL-safe characters must be escaped.

data.name: Delete
count
data.description: The amount of feed entries to return. If the parameter is specified, then {p} and {ps} are ignored.

data.name: dir
data.description: The direction of the order for the field specified in {order}. If the parameter is not specified or provided anything else than "asc" or "desc", then it defaults to "asc".

data.name: id
data.description: The unique identification number of a seed in Feedr. It is required if {link} is not provided.

data.name: link
data.description: Feed url with all non-alphanumeric characters escaped. It is required if {id} is not provided.

data.name: order
data.description: The name of the field to order by.

data.name: p
data.description: The page number. If the parameter is greater than the total number of pages, the method returns an empty array. If the parameter is not provided, the method returns all seeds and {ps} is ignored.

data.name: ps
data.description: The page size. The amount of seeds returned is equal to or less than the parameter. The parameter is ignored, if {p} is not provided. If the parameter is not provided, then it defaults to 20.

data.name: smr
data.description: The flag that specifies whether feed entries summaries must be returned.
The method returns the set of feed entries for the seed of the provided link.

data.name: p
data.description: The page number. If the parameter is greater than the total number of pages, the method returns an empty array. If the parameter is not provided, the method returns all seeds and {ps} is ignored.

data.name: ps
data.description: The page size. The amount of seeds returned is equal to or less than the parameter. The parameter is ignored, if {p} is not provided. If the parameter is not provided, then it defaults to 20.
